# Page Layouts

Use the shared layout system for all page sections. Max content width is **lg** (`Container` → `max-w-[var(--width-container-lg)]` / 64rem).

## Structure rules

- **Header and Footer** are full-width; inner content uses `Container`
- **All other sections** use `Section` (wraps `Container`) or `Container` directly
- Prefer **Grid** for layout; see `grid-first-layout.mdc`
- Use `Link` for all links (supports `href`, Prismic `field`, and `target`)

## Layout components

| Layer | Component | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Atom | `Container` | lg max-width + horizontal padding |
| Atom | `AspectMedia` | 16:9 image or video |
| Atom | `Link` | Unified link with target support |
| Molecule | `RichText` | Formatted Prismic rich text output |
| Molecule | `SectionIntro` | Centered title → subtitle → text → link |
| Molecule | `TextImage` | 50/50 grid; image always above text on mobile |
| Molecule | `ListingCard` | Card with image, title, Prismic/URL link |
| Organism | `Section` | Full-width section + `Container` |
| Organism | `MediaBlock`, `TextImageBlock`, `ListingBlock`, `SectionIntroBlock`, `RichTextBlock` | Composed page sections |

## Rich text

- Always render Prismic structured text through `RichText` (never raw `PrismicRichText` in pages/slices)
- Inline links inside rich text use the shared `Link` atom via `richTextComponents`

## Listing links

- Prismic **Link** fields support internal document selection or external URLs
- Pass `linkField` to `ListingCard` / `Link`; optional `linkLabel` overrides button text

## Checklist for new sections

- [ ] Wrapped in `Section` or uses `Container` (not raw `max-w-*` on sections)
- [ ] Links use `Link` with `target` when opening externally
- [ ] Rich text uses `RichText` molecule
- [ ] Responsive layout uses grid (`lg:grid-cols-3` for listings, `md:grid-cols-2` for text/image)
